---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Socionics Dichotomies">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Socionics Dichotomies</h1>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">Classical Jungian Dichotomies</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Extraversion / Introversion</strong> – Focus of attention: external environment vs. inner world</li>
    <li><strong>Logic / Ethics</strong> – Decision-making: impersonal reasoning vs. personal values</li>
    <li><strong>Intuition / Sensing</strong> – Information gathering: abstract patterns vs. concrete facts</li>
    <li><strong>Rationality / Irrationality</strong> – Behavior: structured and planned vs. adaptive and spontaneous</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">Reinin Dichotomies</h2>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Reinin dichotomies are 15 additional trait pairs derived from combining classical dichotomies. They add depth to type analysis and behavior understanding.
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Static / Dynamic</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Aristocratic / Democratic</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Tactical / Strategic</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Positivist / Negativist</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Judicious / Decisive</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Process / Result</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Carefree / Farsighted</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Constructivist / Emotivist</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Askers / Declarers</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Subjectivist / Objectivist</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Involutionary / Evolutionary</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Yielding / Obstinate</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Serious / Merry</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Comparativist / Absolutist</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Demonstrative / Resultative</strong></li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mt-4">
    These traits are used mainly in advanced Socionics to refine understanding of each type beyond Model A.
  </p>
</Layout>
